<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-107-208  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 107 208.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Nov 13 1989 v3 n46 p1(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GSA includes stringent rules in Fedlink DPA. (General ServicesAdministration, Federal Library and Information Network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smithmidford, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The General Services Administration (GSA) is strictly curtailingprocurement of the Library of Congress's Federal Library andInformation Network (Fedlink) program.andP;  The restrictions followconfirmation that Fedlink was used by military agencies in 1988 toplace $45 million in orders for non-library equipment andservices, thereby bypassing federal procurement rules.andP;  The GSAhas removed procurement of computer equipment from Fedlinkauthority, has imposed a co-signing requirement for Fedlink ordersexceeding $25,000, and will now review top Fedlink contracts toensure they follow applicable rules.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Government ContractsGovernment AgencyManagementLibrariesPurchasing SystemsUnited States. General Services AdministrationUnited States. Library of Congress.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>